claim.claim-text:
1. A sole structure for an article of footwear, the sole structure comprising:
a midsole defining a first cavity tapering from a first aperture to a first bottom wall and a second cavity tapering from a second aperture to a second bottom wall, the first cavity disposed closer to an anterior end of the midsole than the second cavity and having a different taper than the second cavity;
a first barrier member formed from a first material and defining a first compartment received by the first cavity and a second compartment received by the second cavity;
a first quantity of particulate matter disposed within the first compartment; and
a second quantity of particulate matter disposed within the second compartment.

11. A sole structure for an article of footwear, the sole structure comprising:
a midsole defining a first cavity extending between a first aperture and a first bottom wall and a second cavity extending between a second aperture and a second bottom wall, at least one of the first bottom wall and the second bottom wall having a third aperture formed therethrough;
a first barrier member formed from a first material and defining a first compartment received by the first cavity and a second compartment received by the second cavity, the first barrier member extending over the third aperture;
a first quantity of particulate matter disposed within the first compartment; and
a second quantity of particulate matter disposed within the second compartment.
